## 🚨 Troubleshooting



### Service won't start
```bash
# Check environment variables

docker-compose config



# View logs

docker-compose logs project-ai



# Validate config

python config_validator.py



# Check .env file exists

ls -la .env
```



### Configuration not loading
```bash
# Verify .env location

pwd && ls .env



# Check environment in container

docker-compose exec project-ai env | grep API_KEY



# Restart with fresh config

docker-compose down && docker-compose up -d
```



### Kubernetes config not applied
```bash
# Check ConfigMap

kubectl get configmap project-ai-config -o yaml



# Check Secret

kubectl get secret project-ai-secrets -o yaml



# Verify pod environment

kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- env | grep API



# Restart deployment

kubectl rollout restart deployment/project-ai
```



### Production validation failing
```bash
# Run validator with details

python config_validator.py



# Common issues:


# - API_KEYS not set → Set in environment


# - JWT_SECRET not set → Set in environment  


# - CORS_ORIGINS='*' → Set specific origins


# - LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG → Set to INFO/WARNING
```

---



## 📊 Configuration Status Check
```bash
# Quick health check

python -c "
from config.settings import Config
from config.settings_manager import SettingsManager

print('API Host:', Config.API_HOST)
print('API Port:', Config.API_PORT)
print('Log Level:', Config.LOG_LEVEL)
print('Environment:', Config.get('ENVIRONMENT', 'unknown'))
"



# Detailed status

python config_validator.py --output status.txt
cat status.txt
```

---



## 🎯 Production Deployment Checklist

- [ ] All secrets generated (not default values)
- [ ] `SECRET_KEY` is random (32+ bytes)
- [ ] `JWT_SECRET` is random (64+ bytes)
- [ ] `API_KEYS` are strong and unique
- [ ] `ENVIRONMENT=production`
- [ ] `LOG_LEVEL=INFO` or `WARNING`
- [ ] `CORS_ORIGINS` specific (not `*`)
- [ ] `DEBUG=false` or unset
- [ ] Configuration validated: `python config_validator.py --fail-on-error`
- [ ] Secrets in secrets manager (not .env file)
- [ ] `.env` not committed to git
- [ ] Database connection secure
- [ ] SSL/TLS enabled
- [ ] Rate limiting enabled
- [ ] Monitoring configured
- [ ] Backup configured

